      "data": {
        "type": "automated_step",
        "label": "Grasp Sample A (atomic close + attach)",
        "description": "ROS `call_service` to `/grasp` (`aithericon_motion_bridge/srv/Grasp`) \u2014 the atomic compound op: actuate the `xarm_gripper` group closed THEN `AttachedCollisionObject` ADD of `sample_a` on `/apply_planning_scene`, both in one call, returning only after both complete. `object_id` is inlined as the literal `sample_a` (the box seeded by `add_sample_a`). `attached == true` proves `sample_a` is now part of the robot's collision body and will ride the gripper through the lift \u2014 which is exactly what the twin then streams. Plain `executor`: rides the held lease. interface_typedefs copied verbatim from demo 37-pick's `grasp`.",
